{"id":60845,"title":"Resident Rounds part III: scleromyxedema: a rare disorder associated with a monoclonal gammopathy.","abstract":"Scleromyxedema is a rare primary cutaneous mucinosis affecting middle-aged adults. It is characterized by dermal mucin deposition with increased collagen in the skin and internal organs. We report a case of a 72-year-old man with classic skin findings of scleromyxedema as well as a monoclonal gammopathy.","date":"2014-05-09","categories":"Hemic and Lymphatic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24809891","annotations":[{"name":"Collagen","weight":0.809719,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Collagen"},{"name":"Organ (anatomy)","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organ_(anatomy)"},{"name":"Dermis","weight":0.650124,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dermis"},{"name":"Skin","weight":0.645101,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.376917,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Viscus","weight":0.370755,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Viscus"},{"name":"Rare disease","weight":0.287896,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rare_disease"},{"name":"Mucin","weight":0.129468,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mucin"},{"name":"Papular mucinosis","weight":0.116968,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Papular_mucinosis"},{"name":"Monoclonal gammopathy","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monoclonal_gammopathy"},{"name":"Monoclonal antibodies","weight":0.0227187,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monoclonal_antibodies"},{"name":"Back to the Future Part III","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Back_to_the_Future_Part_III"},{"name":"Residency (medicine)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Residency_(medicine)"},{"name